title: PML-N candidate Muhammad Khan wins PB-14 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) candidate Muhammad Khan has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-14, Naseerabad-II by securing 22,639 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Peopleâ€™s Party candidate Ghulam Rasool who bagged 18,948 votes.
Overall voters turnout remained 45.01 percent.
